# TestFeed SEO & Content Creation Rules

## Critical SEO Requirements

### Frontmatter Schema for Blogs
```yaml
---
title: "SEO Title with Primary Keyword | TestFeed"  # Under 60 chars
description: "140-160 character meta description with primary keyword and compelling CTA"
articleTitle: "Display H1 Title (can be longer/different from SEO title)"
publishDate: 2025-MM-DD
updatedDate: 2025-MM-DD  # Add when making content updates
author: "Author Name"
excerpt: "Brief summary for previews and social sharing"
tags: ["primary-keyword", "secondary-keyword", "tertiary-keyword"]  # MAX 3 tags
minutesRead: XX
draft: false
relatedPosts: ["slug-1", "slug-2"]  # Exactly 2 related post slugs
schemaMarkup:
  type: "BlogPosting"
  properties:
    headline: "Same as articleTitle"
    description: "Same as meta description"
    datePublished: "2025-MM-DD"
    author:
      "@type": "Person"
      name: "Author Name"
    publisher:
      "@type": "Organization"
      name: "TestFeed"
---
```

### Frontmatter Schema for Tools
```yaml
---
title: "Tool Name - TestFeed"
description: "140-160 character description with primary keywords and tool benefits"
icon: "lucide-icon-name"
schemaMarkup:
  type: "WebPage"
  properties:
    name: "Tool Name"
    description: "Same as meta description"
    url: "/tools/tool-slug"
---
```

## Content Structure Rules

### ❌ NEVER use H1 in markdown content
- Do NOT use `# Title` in markdown content
- The `articleTitle` from frontmatter automatically becomes the H1
- Start content with H2 (`## Section Title`) or body text
- This prevents duplicate H1 SEO issues

### ✅ Proper Heading Hierarchy
```markdown
## Main Section (H2)
### Subsection (H3)
#### Detail Section (H4)
```

## SEO Optimization

### Meta Descriptions
- **Length**: 140-160 characters (optimal for search snippets)
- **Include**: Primary keyword, compelling benefit, subtle CTA
- **Test**: Count characters including spaces

### Tags Strategy
- **Maximum**: 3 tags per post/tool
- **Format**: lowercase, hyphen-separated
- **Focus**: Primary keyword, secondary keyword, category

### Slug Guidelines
- **Format**: lowercase, hyphen-separated
- **Include**: Primary keyword
- **Length**: 3-5 words maximum

### Internal Linking
- **Related Posts**: Every blog must have exactly 2 related posts
- **Strategic**: Link to complementary content, not similar content

## Content Writing

### Hyperlinks
- **External links**: Use normal markdown syntax `[text](url)`
- **Internal links**: Use relative paths `/blog/slug/` or `/tools/slug/`
- **Note**: External links automatically open in new tabs (no need for `target="_blank"`)

### Formatting
- **Bold**: `**important text**` for key concepts
- **Italic**: `*emphasis*` for subtle emphasis
- **Code**: `` `inline code` `` for technical terms
- **Highlights**: `<span class='highlight'>text</span>` for key phrases

## Quality Checklist

Before publishing, verify:
- [ ] No `# H1` used in markdown content
- [ ] SEO title under 60 characters with primary keyword
- [ ] Meta description 140-160 characters with keyword
- [ ] Exactly 3 relevant tags
- [ ] Related posts specified (2 posts for blogs)
- [ ] All schema fields completed
- [ ] Updated date added if editing existing content

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### ❌ SEO Anti-Patterns
- Using `# H1` in markdown content
- Meta descriptions over 160 or under 140 characters
- More than 3 tags per post
- Duplicate H1s between title and content
- Missing related posts for blogs

### ❌ Content Anti-Patterns
- Starting with generic introductions
- Missing internal links to related content
- No clear value proposition in first paragraph

Remember: These rules ensure consistency, SEO optimization, and user value. When in doubt, prioritize user experience while maintaining technical SEO requirements.